    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="92"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363/250: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-10T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 10, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>208. Refer Legation’s strictly confidential despatch 1431 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >1441</hi>], February 25,<note n="1" xml:id="d92fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    reporting negotiations by Señor Madrigal, President of the Banco de Brazil
                        Nacional,<note n="2" xml:id="d92fn2">Actually Ramón Madrigal Antillon was
                        president of the Banco Nacional de Costa Rica.</note> for the importation of
                    50,000 gallons of gasoline from Mexico.<note n="3" xml:id="d92fn3">For
                        correspondence concerning petroleum exports from Mexico, see letter of
                        August 31 from the Ambassador in Mexico, and instruction No. 4606, October
                        23, to the Ambassador in Mexico, <ref target="#pg_463">pp. 463</ref> and
                            <ref target="#pg_465">465</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I have today been asked by Mr. Jorge Escalante, head of the Costa Rican Gasoline
                    Rationing Board, if such importation should be made whether there will be a
                    corresponding reduction in the regular quota allotted for delivery to Costa Rica
                    by the Latin American Supply Committee.<note n="4" xml:id="d92fn4">The Petroleum
                        Supply Committee for Latin America, with headquarters in New York.</note> It
                    is understood that the importation in question would be made in bulk and would
                    be merely the first of regular shipments.</p>
                <pb facs="0106" n="92" xml:id="pg_92"/>
                <p>Since Señor Madrigal is now in Mexico arranging this deal, it is urgent that I be
                    informed immediately whether all petroleum importations outside the pool will be
                    deducted from pool deliveries.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
